## Phase 1: Scaffold (Saturday Morning, 2-3 hours)\
\
### Step 3: Claude Code \'97 Init the Project\
\
Open terminal, create the project:\
\
```bash\
claude-code "Create a Next.js 14 app with:\
- App router\
- Supabase auth (Google OAuth + email/password)\
- Stripe integration ($9.99/mo Pro plan, 3 free generations for unauthed users)\
- Tailwind CSS\
- OpenAI SDK\
- Vercel Blob for asset storage\
- Basic layout: header with logo, main content area, footer\
- Environment variables template for SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, STRIPE_SECRET_KEY, STRIPE_PRICE_ID, OPENAI_API_KEY, BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN"\
```\
\
### Step 4: Supabase Setup\
\
In Supabase dashboard:\
1. Create new project: `snapbrand`\
2. Enable Google OAuth provider\
3. Create tables:\
\
```sql\
-- Brand kits generated\
create table brand_kits (\
  id uuid default gen_random_uuid() primary key,\
  user_id uuid references auth.users,\
  business_name text not null,\
  business_type text, -- "restaurant", "coaching", "ecommerce", etc.\
  description text,\
  generated_data jsonb, -- full AI output (colors, fonts, taglines, etc.)\
  hero_image_url text, -- uploaded product photo if any\
  created_at timestamptz default now()\
);\
\
-- Track generations for free tier limiting\
create table generations (\
  id uuid default gen_random_uuid() primary key,\
  user_id uuid references auth.users,\
  session_id text, -- for anonymous users\
  created_at timestamptz default now()\
);\
\
-- Enable RLS\
alter table brand_kits enable row level security;\
alter table generations enable row level security;\
```\
\
### Step 5: Stripe Setup\
\
In Stripe dashboard:\
1. Create product: "SnapBrand Pro"\
2. Create price: $9.99/month recurring\
3. Set up webhook endpoint: `/api/webhooks/stripe`\
4. Events to listen for: `checkout.session.completed`, `customer.subscription.deleted`\
\
You've done this exact flow with CardSnap ($9.99/mo) \'97 same pattern, copy the webhook handler logic.\
