## Phase 2: Core Product Flow (Saturday Afternoon, 3-4 hours)\
\
### Step 6: The Input Page (Landing Page IS the Product)\
\
Like Photo AI \'97 the landing page IS the conversion tool. No separate "app" page. User lands, sees the tool, uses it.\
\
```\
Claude Code prompt:\
"Build the homepage with:\
1. H1: 'Generate Your Complete Brand Kit in 60 Seconds'\
2. Subtitle: 'AI-powered brand identity for your business. Logo concepts, colors, typography, social templates \'97 no designer needed.'\
3. Input form with:\
   - Business name (required)\
   - Business type dropdown: Restaurant, E-commerce, Coaching, Real Estate, Fitness, Photography, Podcast, SaaS, Agency, Other\
   - One-line description (required, placeholder: 'Artisan coffee roastery in Brooklyn')\
   - Optional: upload product photo or logo inspiration\
   - Style preference: Modern & Clean, Bold & Playful, Luxury & Elegant, Warm & Organic, Tech & Minimal\
4. Big CTA button: '\uc0\u10024  Generate My Brand Kit'\
5. Below: '3 free generations \'97 no sign up required'\
6. Social proof: counter showing total kits generated"\
```\
\
### Step 7: The AI Generation Engine \'97 `/api/generate`\
\
This is the core. One API route that calls OpenAI and returns a structured brand kit.\
\
```\
Claude Code prompt:\
"Create /api/generate route that:\
1. Accepts: businessName, businessType, description, stylePreference, optional imageUrl\
2. Calls OpenAI GPT-4o with a structured output prompt that returns JSON:\
   - brand_name_options: 3 variations/taglines\
   - color_palette: primary, secondary, accent, background, text (hex codes + names)\
   - typography: heading font (Google Fonts), body font, size scale\
   - tagline_options: 3 tagline suggestions\
   - brand_voice: 2-3 sentence brand voice description\
   - logo_concepts: 3 text descriptions of logo concepts (we'll generate images separately)\
   - social_templates: descriptions for Instagram post, story, LinkedIn banner\
3. Then calls DALL-E 3 to generate:\
   - 1 logo concept image (simple, icon-style, on white background)\
   - 1 social media mockup\
4. Stores images to Vercel Blob\
5. Saves full result to Supabase brand_kits table\
6. Returns the complete kit JSON to frontend\
7. Rate limit: check generations table \'97 max 3 per session/user without auth, unlimited for Pro"\
```\
\
**The OpenAI prompt is everything.** Here's the system prompt structure:\
\
```\
You are an expert brand strategist and designer. Given a business description, generate a complete brand identity system. Return ONLY valid JSON.\
\
The brand kit must be cohesive \'97 colors, typography, and voice should all tell the same story. Think about:\
- What emotions should this brand evoke?\
- Who is the target customer?\
- What differentiates this from competitors in the same vertical?\
\
Be specific with hex codes, Google Font names, and actionable descriptions.\
```\
\
### Step 8: The Results Page \'97 `/results/[id]`\
\
Shareable results page (same pattern as CardSnap's `/results/[id]`).\
\
```\
Claude Code prompt:\
"Create a results page at /results/[id] that:\
1. Fetches brand kit data from Supabase by ID\
2. Displays the full brand kit in beautiful cards:\
   - Color Palette: actual color swatches with hex codes, copy-on-click\
   - Typography: live preview using Google Fonts embed\
   - Logo Concept: DALL-E generated image\
   - Taglines: 3 options displayed\
   - Brand Voice: description card\
   - Social Template: mockup preview\
3. Download section (gated for Pro):\
   - 'Download Brand Kit PDF' button\
   - 'Download Color Palette' button\
   - 'Download Logo (PNG)' button\
   - If not Pro: clicking shows auth modal \uc0\u8594  Stripe checkout\
4. Share button: copy link to clipboard\
5. 'Generate Another' CTA at bottom\
6. Meta tags for social sharing (OG image = the logo concept)"\
```\
