## Phase 3: Programmatic SEO (Saturday Evening, 2-3 hours)\
\
This is the Levels + Schneider play. This is where the money is.\
\
### Step 9: Vertical Landing Pages\
\
Create programmatic pages for every business type. Same pattern as movieslike.app's "movies like [X]" pages and Photo AI's photo pack pages.\
\
```\
Claude Code prompt:\
"Create a dynamic route at /brand-kit/[vertical]/page.tsx that:\
1. Has a verticals data file with 30+ entries, each containing:\
   - slug: 'restaurant', 'real-estate-agent', 'fitness-coach', etc.\
   - title: 'AI Brand Kit for Restaurants'\
   - h1: 'Create Your Restaurant Brand Identity in 60 Seconds'\
   - description: SEO-optimized description for this vertical\
   - specific_prompts: example descriptions for this vertical\
   - pain_points: why this vertical needs branding help\
   - example_colors: suggested palette for the vertical\
2. Each page renders:\
   - Unique H1 targeting '[vertical] brand kit' keyword\
   - 3-4 paragraphs of vertical-specific content (generated once via OpenAI, stored in data file)\
   - The same generate form, pre-filled with the business type\
   - Example brand kit preview for that vertical\
   - FAQ section (3-5 Q&As specific to that vertical)\
3. Generates proper meta tags, title, description for each vertical\
4. Add all verticals to sitemap.xml"\
```\
\
**Target verticals (start with 30, expand to 100+):**\
\
Tier 1 (high volume): restaurant, real estate agent, personal trainer, life coach, photographer, podcast, e-commerce store, beauty salon, law firm, dental practice\
\
Tier 2 (medium volume): coffee shop, yoga studio, tattoo shop, wedding planner, dog groomer, barber shop, nail salon, florist, bakery, food truck\
\
Tier 3 (long tail, zero competition): mobile detailing, pressure washing, junk removal, notary public, tutoring service, bookkeeper, virtual assistant, pet sitter, handyman, cleaning service\
